<!-- {{{ --> <!-- Lecture notes -->
<h4> Selected Lecture Notes and Other Reading </h4>
A complete set of lecture  notes are presented in class, but the 
following sets of notes may provide a useful base for your studies.
<ul><li>
Some handy notes on 
<a href="AlgebraNotes.pdf">
SETS, COMPLEX NUMBERS,
SEQUENCES AND SERIES, and DIFFERENCE EQUATIONS (provisional version)</a>
- i.e. notes on ALL topics covered in the course except Matrices
(for Matrices, all notes must be taken in class).
</li><li>
Some handy notes on 
<a href="X1AlgRels.pdf"> RELATIONS (provisional version) </a> 
</li><li>
Some notes for more advanced students wishing to make 
<a href="http://www.staff.city.ac.uk/~ra359/psfiles/a3.pdf">
Algebra THE NEXT STEP (provisional version)
</a>. 
These notes have been used in the past to help X1 students prepare for 
the X2 Linear Algebra course. They are not currently being used for this
purpose, and the `Treasure hunt' refered to in the notes is not happening this
year. 
However, you may find some of these notes very useful as 
collateral/support  material for X1 Algebra!  
</li><li>
Visit Dr Cox's X2 Linear Algebra homepage for some useful notes on matrices (and 
much more besides!). 
</li>
</ul>

<!-- }}} -->
<!-- {{{ --> <!-- Exercises -->
<h4>Exercises</h4>
Once you have attempted an exercise from the lists below 
you may consult your Personal Tutor, or your Friday Tutor, in tutorial, 
to check that you have it right (or for help, if you got stuck!).
Always take your lecture notes to tutorials.
<ul>
<li>
<a href="X1AlgEx01.pdf">
All Exercise sheets in a single pdf file (provisional version)
</a> Print off as much as you like! 
Sets of sheets for the individual sections of the course are below.
See NEWS section for suggestions on which questions 
you should now be able to do. 
</li><li>
<a href="X1AlgEx_Matrices.pdf">
Exercises on Matrices </a>
</li><li>
<a href="http://www.city.ac.uk/mathematics/algebra/X1Algebra/X1AlgEx_Complex.pdf">
Exercises on Complex Numbers </a>
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://www.city.ac.uk/mathematics/algebra/X1Algebra/X1AlgEx_Series.pdf">
Exercises on Series </a>
</li>
<li>
<a href="X1AlgEx_Relations.pdf"> Exercises on Sets and Relations </a>
</li>
</ul>

